        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued November 25 at 7:24AM EST by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 724 AM EST, a strong thunderstorm was near Mentone, or 8 miles
northeast of Fort Payne, moving east at 50 mph.

HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind and heavy rain.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects. Heavy rain may cause temporary
street flooding especially in poor drainage areas.

Locations impacted include...
Lafayette, Summerville, Trion, La Fayette, Menlo, Naomi, Center Post,
Rising Fawn, Subligna, Suttles Mill, Noble, Linwood, Cloudland,
Berryton, Cloudland Canyon State Park, Cooper Heights, James H. Floyd
State Park, and Rock Spring.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. Motorists should
slow down and be prepared for possible loss of control due to
hydroplaning.</instruction>
